# Five transformation imperatives determine retail competitive positioning
@type: comparison

@compare:
  header: Imperative | Current Maturity | Target State | Investment Required
  row: Unified customer data platform | Fragmented (siloed by channel) | Single customer view across all touchpoints | $18M
  row: Real-time inventory visibility | Store-level batch (daily) | SKU-level real-time across all nodes | $12M
  row: Personalization at scale | Rule-based segmentation | ML-driven individual personalization | $8M
  row: Digital marketing efficiency | Cookie-dependent attribution | First-party data + incrementality testing | $5M
  row: Store-digital integration | Separate P&Ls and teams | Unified omnichannel operations | Organizational

@exhibit: Exhibit 2 — Transformation Roadmap Investment Summary
@source: Bain analysis; vendor RFP benchmarks, 2024

@notes: The customer data platform is the foundation for every other initiative. Sequence it first — nothing else delivers full value without unified data.

---

# Three transformation phases unlock value progressively over 30 months
@type: timeline

@step: Phase 1 (0–9 months) | Data Foundation | CDP implementation, inventory integration, digital marketing cleanup
@step: Phase 2 (9–20 months) | Personalization | ML-driven recommendations, targeted promotions, loyalty overhaul
@step: Phase 3 (20–30 months) | Operations Integration | Store-digital unified P&L, real-time replenishment, endless aisle

@source: Bain Retail Digital Transformation Methodology, 2024

@notes: Phase 1 generates $180M in value through markdown reduction and media efficiency before personalization is even live. This funds Phase 2.

