# Transformation delivers $2.1B in cumulative value over five years
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Revenue Uplift ($1.2B)
  - Personalization drives 8% lift in digital conversion
  - Loyalty redesign adds $280M in incremental spend
  - Omnichannel customers spend 2.3× more than single-channel
  - Reduced stockouts add $190M in recovered revenue

@col:
  ## Cost Reduction ($0.9B)
  - Inventory optimization reduces working capital by $320M
  - Marketing efficiency gains: $240M in reallocated spend
  - Store labor optimization via traffic forecasting: $180M
  - Returns reduction through better sizing/fit: $160M

@notes: Investors typically anchor on revenue uplift. The cost savings are equally large and more certain — lead with them in CFO conversations.

